ZH: 他在评价比赛时往往偏袒自己支持的队伍。
EN: He tends to be biased towards the team he supports when judging a match.

ZH: 这位裁判一直偏袒主队，让客队的球员感到不公平。
EN: The referee has been consistently biased towards the home team, making the away players feel unfair.

ZH: 有些人会因为亲戚关系而偏袒某人。
EN: Some people may be biased towards someone due to their family relationship.

ZH: 她对他的想法总是偏袒的，不愿意听取别人的意见。
EN: She is always biased towards his ideas, refusing to listen to others' opinions.

ZH: 当两个朋友争执时，我们不能偏袒其中的任何一方。
EN: When two friends argue, we should not be biased towards either side.

ZH: 这个老师总是偏袒一些学生，而对其他人过于苛刻。
EN: This teacher always favors some students while being too harsh on others.

ZH: 他的偏袒让其他团队成员感到很不公平。
EN: His bias made other team members feel very unfair.

ZH: 作为公众人物，他不应该偏袒任何政治立场。
EN: As a public figure, he should not be biased towards any political stance.

ZH: 在裁决案件时，法官不应该偏袒任何一方。
EN: Judges should not be biased towards any party when ruling on a case.

ZH: 媒体报道应该客观公正，不应该偏袒任何一方。
EN: Media reports should be objective and impartial, not biased towards any party.

ZH: 老板很偏袒她的好朋友，而对其他员工很苛刻。
EN: The boss favors her close friend while being very strict on other employees.

ZH: 我们要努力消除对性别、种族、宗教的偏袒。
EN: We should strive to eliminate bias towards gender, race, and religion.

ZH: 这家公司总是偏袒拥有政治背景的员工。
EN: This company always favors employees with political backgrounds.

ZH: 领导不应该偏袒某个部门，而应该平等对待所有部门。
EN: Leaders should not be biased towards one department, but treat all departments equally.

ZH: 我们的法律应该保证公正，不应该发生偏袒的现象。
EN: Our laws should guarantee fairness and should not show any bias.

ZH: 对于所有选手来说，评委都应该公正，不偏袒任何一方。
EN: Judges should be fair and impartial to all contestants, not biased towards any one.

ZH: 我们要警惕个人偏袒对于工作带来的负面影响。
EN: We should be vigilant about the negative impact of personal bias on work.

ZH: 教育系统应该消除偏袒，确保每个学生都接受平等对待。
EN: The education system should eliminate bias and ensure that every student is treated equally.

ZH: 在处理纠纷时，仲裁员应该保持中立，不偏袒任何一方。
EN: Arbitrators should remain neutral and not biased towards any party when resolving disputes.
